-- MOVES-Integro Group makes three senior appointments
-- 
-- Thu Oct 30, 2014 02:12PM EDT
-- None



Oct 30 (Reuters) - Risk management firm Integro Group said it made three senior appointments in its Portland, New York and Chicago offices.

Kate Bauer joined as vice president in casualty practice at the Portland office, responsible for executing customized risk strategies and solutions, Integro said in a statement.  She previously worked with risk advisory firm Marsh USA. Robert Stearns joined Integro's global marine practice as a principal in New York from financial services firm Starr Companies. He will be responsible for the servicing of Integro's marine liability and marine hull insurance programs.